# Trivy ignore list for pg-volume-backup.
#
# CVEs listed here have fix versions in Trivy's DB but the patched packages
# are not yet published to the Amazon Linux 2023 repository.  `dnf upgrade`
# runs at every build and will pick up patches automatically when they land.
# Remove each entry once `dnf check-update` confirms the fix is available.
#
# Verified 2026-05-04: `dnf check-update` inside the image exits 0 (no
# updates available for glibc or python3/python3-libs).

# glibc / glibc-common / glibc-minimal-langpack
# HIGH — DoS via iconv() with specific character sets
# Installed: 2.34-231.amzn2023.0.3; Trivy fix: 2.34-231.amzn2023.0.4
CVE-2026-4046

# python3 / python3-libs
# HIGH — incomplete control-character validation in http.cookies
# Installed: 3.9.25-1.amzn2023.0.4; Trivy fix: 3.9.25-1.amzn2023.0.5
CVE-2026-3644

# python3 / python3-libs
# HIGH — arbitrary code execution via command injection in webbrowser.open()
# Installed: 3.9.25-1.amzn2023.0.4; Trivy fix: 3.9.25-1.amzn2023.0.5
CVE-2026-4786

# python3 / python3-libs
# HIGH — arbitrary code execution / info disclosure via use-after-free in
# decompression; Installed: 3.9.25-1.amzn2023.0.4; Trivy fix: 3.9.25-1.amzn2023.0.5
CVE-2026-6100
